<br>
Which isnt all that unusual hehehe.<br>
<br>
My own contribution is simple. I feel the Warder should be a much larger source of the DPS than the character. After all, the name of the class is Beastlord, not &quot;Monk guy with a pet to help him do extra damage.&quot;  I think the spells Beastlords get for augmenting their pets coupled with the debuffs and dot's vs the mobs, (admittedly the dot's aren't spectacular) make for a very clear theory of what this class is meant to do.<br>
<br>
1. See mob.<br>
2. Slow mob.<br>
3. Send in pet, as mob now wants you dead.<br>
4. Continue to debuff mob.<br>
5. DoT mob.<br>
6. Mob is now chewing you up, so fight back.<br>
7. When fight is over, heal up and do it again.<br>
<br>
Now of course, Verant saw that this makes every Beastlord in the world want to solo, as they are well made for it, (I know the signs, mages used to be like this) so they added something.<br>
<br>
8. Provide your group with extra mana regen and HP regen<br>
<br>
Funny, cuz mages got this one :<br>
<br>
8. Provide your group/raid with extra mana via rods, and CoH latecomers<br>
<br>
Anyhow, thats an issue for another debate.  I stand firm on my position however.  Put DA back in for my gator, he needs to do a lot of damage. God knows my troll can't do it alone.  <br>
